main event: The USS Newell observed 5 unlit objects from a position approximately 25-12 North 163-50 West while on course 123. The objects fell ahead of the ship from an elevation of about 45 degrees to 10 degrees.
interesting points: The objects were observed from the USS Newell while the ship was at sea.
The objects were unlit and fell ahead of the ship's course.
The objects were observed at an elevation range of about 45 degrees to 10 degrees.
The sighting occurred at a position approximately 25-12 North 163-50 West.
The report appears to be from Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated UFO sightings.
